THE GM's MASTER KEY: HOW TO USE THIS MAP
The Triad of Consequence is Law: At each Gate, the party chooses one Fire. You, as the GM, assign one of the remaining two to Krusp. The third Fire is Ignored and its villain succeeds, advancing their Apocalypse Clock.
Krusp's Attrition: Krusp's team always succeeds, but they pay a heavy, non-Daedric price. Track their compounding injuries and losses. This is the narrative engine for his eventual breaking point.
The World Decays: The consequences of Ignored Fires are permanent. Mark them on your world map. The players should feel the world getting smaller, darker, and more dangerous because of the choices they didn't make.
Personal Arcs are Fuel: The Fires are not random; they are deliberately designed to intersect with the party's personal motivations. A player's desire to advance their own story becomes a driving force in the group's strategic decisions.

